\DOC find_consts_thy

\TYPE {find_consts_thy : search function}

\SYNOPSIS
Searches in the theories in list {thl} for a constant of a given type {ty}.

\DESCRIBE
Given a type {ty} and a list of theorie names {thl} searches the theories with
names from {thl} for constants of type {ty}.

\FAILURE
Fails if {ty} is not a valid HOL type.

\EXAMPLE
If we run
{
  find_consts_thy ["bool"] ``:'a -> 'a set -> bool``;
}

we get

{
   > val it = [“$IN”]: term list
}

and for

{

   find_consts_thy ["arithmetic"] ``:num -> num -> num``;
}

we get

{
   > val it = [“$*”, “$+”, “$-”, “ABS_DIFF”, “$DIV”, “$**”, “MAX”, “MIN”, “$MOD”]:
}

\SEEALSO
bossLib.find_consts, DB.apropos, DB.find
\ENDDOC